        "summary": {
          "diffs": [
            {
              "file": "bench-artifacts/cache-api.md",
              "patch": "Index: bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\n===================================================================\n--- bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\t\n+++ bench-artifacts/cache-api.md\t\n@@ -0,0 +1,61 @@\n+# Cache API\n+\n+## createCache()\n+\n+Creates a new cache instance.\n+\n+```js\n+import { createCache } from 'cache-api'\n+```\n+\n+## Methods\n+\n+Returns an object with the following cache methods:\n+\n+### get(key)\n+\n+Retrieves a value from the cache by key. Returns the cached value or `undefined` if the key doesn't exist.\n+\n+```js\n+const cachedValue = cache.get('my-key')\n+```\n+\n+### set(key, value)\n+\n+Stores a value in the cache. Returns the set value.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.set('my-key', 'my-value')\n+```\n+\n+### delete(key)\n+\n+Removes a value from the cache by key. Returns the deleted value or what was deleted.\n+\n+```js\n+const deletedValue = cache.delete('my-key')\n+```\n+\n+### clear()\n+\n+Clears all cache entries.\n+\n+```js\n+cache.clear()\n+```\n+\n+---\n+\n+**Implementation:** A `Map` instance is used internally to store key-value pairs.\n+\n+```js\n+export function createCache() {\n+  const values = new Map()\n+  return {\n+    get(key) { return values.get(key) },\n+    set(key, value) { values.set(key, value); return value },\n+    delete(key) { return values.delete(key) },\n+    clear() { values.clear() }\n+  }\n+}\n+```\n\\ No newline at end of file\n",
              "additions": 61,
              "deletions": 0,
              "status": "added"
            }
          ]
        },
